Female genitalia (Fig. 29
B-G
): tignum long, narrow, slightly bent, with central canal; anterior sclerotization narrow, posterior sclerotization well delineated, narrower than anterior (Fig. 29B). Vaginal palpi elongate, basally strongly sclerotized, each with approximately eight setae at apex (Fig. 29C). Palpi pointed at apex, enlarged at last third but thinned at apex, situated close together and merged anteriorly for more than half of their length. Posterior sclerotization of vaginal palpi with straight sides. Spermatheca curved, with receptacle and pump not differentiated from each other, receptacle longer than pump. Apex of pump with relatively thick spoon-like projection. Spermathecal duct short, widest at base, without coils, making narrow loop (Fig. 29E).
